Luka Modric reportedly has two offers on the table to leave Real Madrid during the summer transfer window. The veteran midfielder has been a hot topic this week after producing a remarkable assist for Rodrygo during Los Blancos’ comeback progression against Chelsea in the Champions League. After the contest, the 36-year-old said that contract talks with Real could wait, stating that he will decide his future year by year.   UNFINISHED BUSINESS: Pep, Klopp in unending fight for…     AFCON 2023 qualifier: Super Eagles know opponents on Tuesday     Super Falcons to know WAFCON group opponents on April 25   According to Spanish journalist Sergio Santos, Real will not have a clear pathway to retain the services of their legendary player for 2022-23. Santos claimed  that Juventus and a club in Qatar have informed his representatives that they want to sign Modric on a free transfer later this year. Despite the interest, Modric is unlikely to make any decision on his future while Real are still competing for silverware.